<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Herbs 40-80 cm tall. Rhizome compact. Leaves basal and cauline, trifoliolate; leaflets lanceolate or narrowly lanceolate, 13-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 cm, apex long acuminate, margin spinous-serrate, base shallowly cordate, terminal leaflet with subequal rounded lobes, lateral leaflets much oblique, inner lobes small, rounded or almost truncate, outer lobes larger, triangle, acuminate or acute, leathery, adaxially glabrous, abaxially densely strigose, densely pubescent, lanose, or glabrous. Flowering stem with 2 opposite or rarely 3 alternate leaves. Inflorescence paniculate, 30-40 cm long, many (up to 200) flowered, glabrous. Flowers small, 6-10 mm in diam. Outer sepals purplish, small, soon falling. Inner sepals white, ovate, 3-4 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5-2.2 mm, apex acute. Petals yellow, calceiform, 2.2-3.2 mm. Stamens ca. 4 mm; anthers ca. 2.5 mm; filaments ca. 1.5 mm. Capsules ca. 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution and habitat">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in south central Chongqing, northeast Guizhou, western Hubei, and western Hunan. It usually occurs in forests, thickets, weedy slopes, and streamsides in valleys, at elevations of 300 to 800 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowers from March to April, and fruits from April to May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="iucn red list category">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">IUCN Red List category.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be designated as nearly threatened (NT) according to IUCN Red List criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, U. K." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" refId="B3" refString="IUCN, 2013. The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2013.9. IUCN Red List Unit, Cambridge, U.K., http://www.iucnredlist.org/ [accessed: 6 June 2014]" title="The IUCN red list of threatened species, version 2013.9" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/" year="2013">IUCN 2013</bibRefCitation>
), because of exploitation for medicinal use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<pageBreakToken pageId="9" pageNumber="10" start="start">Epimedium</pageBreakToken>
borealiguizhouense
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of series 
<taxonomicName genus="Brachycerae" lsidName="Brachycerae" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brachycerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stearn. Within this series, it is particularly similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1998" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium myrianthum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrianthum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epimedium myrianthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stearn, but both are obviously different in the shape of the leaflets: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears lanceolate or narrowly lanceolate leaflets with the base of terminal leaflet shallowly cordate, the lateral leaflet is much more oblique with the inner lobe much smaller and rounded or almost truncate and the outer lobe triangular and acuminate or acute, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stearn" authorityYear="1998" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium myrianthum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrianthum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epimedium myrianthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has narrowly ovate leaflets with the base moderately cordate with a narrow sinus and the lateral leaflet is oblique with the lobes rounded or acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known only from the type locality, Yanhe, Guizhou. According to herbarium and field investigations, new localities of the species are recorded for Chongqing, Hubei, and Hunan. Furthermore, the indumentum on the abaxial surface of the leaflets varies from densely strigose to densely pubescent, lanose to glabrous. In addition, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium sagittatum subsp. var. var. oblongifoliolatum" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="sagittatum" subSpecies="var." variety="oblongifoliolatum">Epimedium sagittatum var. oblongifoliolatum</taxonomicName>
published in Flora Hubeiensis (
<bibRefCitation author="Fu, SX" journalOrPublisher="Flora Hubeiensis" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="403 - 411" refId="B1" refString="Fu, SX, 2001. . Flora Hubeiensis Vol. 1: 403 - 411" volume="Vol. 1" year="2001">Fu 2001</bibRefCitation>
) is the same species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Z. He &amp; Y. K. Yang" authorityYear="1993" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Berberidaceae" genus="Epimedium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epimedium borealiguizhouense" order="Ranunculales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealiguizhouense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epimedium borealiguizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is synonymized here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
